dk.brics.string.intermediate
Class Application

java.lang.Object
  dk.brics.string.intermediate.Application

public class Application
extends Object

The root of an intermediate program. The application contains Method objects, which in turn contain Statement objects. The application is responsible for creating new variables and fields when requested, and must distribute unique keys to variables, methods, and statements.

A robust structure of an intermediate program is strictly enforced by these classes. The following invariants are enforced (some only when assertion are enabled):

  • A method belongs to exactly one application.
  • A statement belongs to exactly one method (after it has been added).
  • A statement S's successor will list S as a predecessor (and vice versa).
  • A statement does not list the same successor or predecessor twice (implemented as a list but works like a set).
  • Methods like Method.getCallSites() and Field.getFieldAssignments() always work, and require no assistance from outside this package.
  • Field variables are only used in FieldReference and FieldAssignment statements.
